{
  "page": "A Son for a Son (TV)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the book chapter, see <a href=\"/index.php/A_Son_for_a_Son\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"A Son for a Son\">A Son for a Son</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:rgb(248, 233, 208);border:none;\">\"A Son for a Son\"</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size: 100%\">\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<td style=\"width:50%;text-align:right;\">Season 2</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">&#160;—&#160;</td>\n<td style=\"width:50%;text-align:left;\">Episode 1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:A_Son_for_a_Son_HOTD.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"A Son for a Son HOTD.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ec/A_Son_for_a_Son_HOTD.jpg/300px-A_Son_for_a_Son_HOTD.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ec/A_Son_for_a_Son_HOTD.jpg/450px-A_Son_for_a_Son_HOTD.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/ec/A_Son_for_a_Son_HOTD.jpg/600px-A_Son_for_a_Son_HOTD.jpg 2x\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original air date</th><td>\nJune 16, 2024</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Running time</th><td>\n59 minutes</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">Credits</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Directed by</th><td class=\"plainlist\">\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Taylor_(director)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Alan Taylor (director)\">Alan Taylor</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Written by</th><td class=\"plainlist\">\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ryan_Condal\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ryan Condal\">Ryan Condal</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">Episode chronology</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<th style=\"width:50%;text-align:center;\">←&#160;Previous</th>\n<th style=\"width:50%;text-align:center;\">Next&#160;→</th>\n</tr><tr style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Black_Queen\" title=\"The Black Queen\">The Black Queen</a>\"</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\"<a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_the_Cruel\" title=\"Rhaenyra the Cruel\">Rhaenyra the Cruel</a>\"</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#f8e9d0;border:none;\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/List_of_House_of_the_Dragon_episodes\" title=\"List of House of the Dragon episodes\">List of episodes</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>\"<b>A Son for a Son</b>\" is the first episode of <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">season two</a> of the HBO <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/medieval_fantasy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:medieval fantasy\">medieval fantasy</a> television series <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>. Running 59 minutes long, it premiered on June 16, 2024. The episode was written by co-creator and showrunner <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ryan_Condal\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ryan Condal\">Ryan Condal</a> and directed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Taylor_(director)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Alan Taylor (director)\">Alan Taylor</a>. Music was composed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramin_Djawadi\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ramin Djawadi\">Ramin Djawadi</a>.\n</p><p>The title of the episode takes its name from the 14th chapter of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> <i>(\"The Dying of the Dragons - A Son for a Son\")</i>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Official_synopsis\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Official synopsis</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Plot\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Plot</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#The_Wall\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Wall</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Storm.27s_End\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Storm's End</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Driftmark\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Driftmark</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Dragonstone\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dragonstone</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#King.27s_Landing\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">King's Landing</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Cast\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Cast</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Starring\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Starring</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Co-starring\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Co-starring</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#Uncredited\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Uncredited</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-14\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Official_synopsis\">Official synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Official synopsis\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>While Rhaenyra struggles to come to terms with her son’s murder, in King’s Landing, Alicent grows concerned that Aegon’s Small Council may lead them to an all-out war. Larys suggests Aegon needs a new Hand, and Rhaenyra arrives at a fateful decision.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Plot\">Plot</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Plot\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Differences_between_Fire_%26_Blood_and_House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"Differences between Fire &amp; Blood and House of the Dragon\">Differences between Fire &amp; Blood and House of the Dragon</a></div>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Wall\">The Wall</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Wall\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a> travels with Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Cregan_Stark\" title=\"Cregan Stark\">Cregan Stark</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> to recruit the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">North</a> for the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">Blacks</a>. Their meeting ends with Cregan pledging 2,000 greybeards to fight for Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> and news of <a href=\"/index.php/Lucerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Lucerys Velaryon\">Lucerys</a>' death arriving by <a href=\"/index.php/Raven\" title=\"Raven\">raven</a>.\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Storm's_End\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Storm.27s_End\">Storm's End</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Storm&#039;s End\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Rhaenyra flies to <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> in search of answers about Luke's death. After a few days of search, she breaks down when she sees the remains of Luke's dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Arrax\" title=\"Arrax\">Arrax</a> tangled in a fisherman's net.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Driftmark\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> thanks <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_of_Hull\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alyn of Hull\">Alyn of Hull</a> for saving his life on the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a> but the young sailor is nervous around his lord.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Dragonstone\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys</a> patrols the <a href=\"/index.php/Gullet\" title=\"Gullet\">Gullet</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a> and enforces the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">Velaryon</a> naval blokade of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. When she comes back to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>, she refuses to go to the capital with <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon</a> to kill <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a> to avenge Luke. She tells her cousin she only recognizes Rhaenyra's authority and that the queen needs time to grieve her son. The blockade arrests a ship bound for the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> with Mysaria on board. She is arrested and brought to Daemon who accuses her of <a href=\"/index.php/Treason\" title=\"Treason\">treason</a> for helping the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">Greens</a> to put <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II</a> on the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>. At a <a href=\"/index.php/Black_council\" title=\"Black council\">Black council</a> meeting, Rhaenyra returns from the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">Stormlands</a> and demands revenge against Aemond. Jacaerys arrives shortly after, bringing news of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Starks</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">Arryns</a> support to Rhaenyra and joins his mother in grieving Lucerys. In the meantime, Daemon offers Mysaria freedom in exchange for helping him recruit assassins in King's Landing.\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"King's_Landing\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"King.27s_Landing\">King's Landing</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: King&#039;s Landing\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Alicent and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a> have engaged in a sexual affair. King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> brings his young son and heir, <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_Targaryen_(son_of_Aegon_II)\" title=\"Jaehaerys Targaryen (son of Aegon II)\">Jaehaerys</a>, to the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> meeting where the Greens discusses their next move against Rhaenyra. Returning to her chambers, Alicent discovers that <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a> has removed all the traitors within her staff and has chosen new servants for the Dowager Queen.\nAegon holds court in the <a href=\"/index.php/Throne_room\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Throne room\">Throne room</a> and attempts to be generous with the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> but he is denied several times by his <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otto_Hightower\" title=\"Otto Hightower\">Otto Hightower</a>. Larys later suggests the king to remove Otto from office.\n</p><p>Daemon sneaks into King's Landing and meets the assassins recommended by Mysaria, a <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_(butcher)\" title=\"Blood (butcher)\">City Watch guard</a> and a <a href=\"/index.php/Cheese_(ratcatcher)\" title=\"Cheese (ratcatcher)\">Red Keep ratcatcher</a>. Daemon bribes them to kill Aemond or if they can not find him \"a son for a son\" will suffice. The assassins infiltrate the castle successfully but fail to locate Aemond in the royal apartments. The ratcatcher finds Queen Helaena and her sleeping children, Jaehaerys and <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaera_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaera Targaryen\">Jaehaera</a>. Helaena tries to bride the duo with her necklace but to not avail, they settle on killing Jaehaerys. Confused as to which of the twins is the boy, they force Helaena to point him out then murder the boy and cut his head. During all the commotion, Helaena takes Jaehaera with her and flees to the safety of her mother's chambers, only to find her in bed with Ser Criston.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e01.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e01.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cast\">Cast</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Cast\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Starring\">Starring</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Starring\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div style=\"column-count:2; column-width:300px;\"> \n<ul><li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matt_Smith\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Matt Smith\">Matt Smith</a> as Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emma_D%27Arcy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Emma D&#39;Arcy\">Emma D'Arcy</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olivia_Cooke\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Olivia Cooke\">Olivia Cooke</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhys_Ifans\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Rhys Ifans\">Rhys Ifans</a> as Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otto_Hightower\" title=\"Otto Hightower\">Otto Hightower</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Toussaint\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Steve Toussaint\">Steve Toussaint</a> as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eve_Best\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Eve Best\">Eve Best</a> as Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fabien_Frankel\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fabien Frankel\">Fabien Frankel</a> as Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matthew_Needham\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Matthew Needham\">Matthew Needham</a> as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonoya_Mizuno\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sonoya Mizuno\">Sonoya Mizuno</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Glynn-Carney\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Tom Glynn-Carney\">Tom Glynn-Carney</a> as King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ewan_Mitchell\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ewan Mitchell\">Ewan Mitchell</a> as Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phia_Saban\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Phia Saban\">Phia Saban</a> as Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Helaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Helaena Targaryen\">Helaena Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_Collett\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Harry Collett\">Harry Collett</a> as Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bethany_Antonia\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Bethany Antonia\">Bethany Antonia</a> as Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Baela_Targaryen\" title=\"Baela Targaryen\">Baela Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phoebe_Campbell\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Phoebe Campbell\">Phoebe Campbell</a> as Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jefferson_Hall_(actor)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Jefferson Hall (actor)\">Jefferson Hall</a> as Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tyland_Lannister\" title=\"Tyland Lannister\">Tyland Lannister</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Kurt_Egyiawan\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kurt Egyiawan\">Kurt Egyiawan</a> as Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kieran_Bew\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Kieran Bew\">Kieran Bew</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abubakar_Salim\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Abubakar Salim\">Abubakar Salim</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn of Hull</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Taylor_(actor)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Tom Taylor (actor)\">Tom Taylor</a> as Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Cregan_Stark\" title=\"Cregan Stark\">Cregan Stark</a></li></ul>\n</div>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Co-starring\">Co-starring</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Son_for_a_Son_(TV)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Co-starring\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div style=\"column-count:2; column-width:300px;\"> \n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Paul_Kennedy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Paul Kennedy\">Paul K